\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 However, two quarter-noter notes were originally notated as extra note-heads on the chords, and there is nothing wrong with letting these be in Voice 1 with the rest of the chord.  The consequence is that Voice 2 drops out early, but this is immaterial in this example.  Furthermore, using our approach it is not necessary to add extra invisible eighth-note rests in the bass staff to counter the eighth-note heads that have moved to the treble staff. \par
